      • setBounds

        public void setBounds​(java.lang.Double southWestLng,
                      java.lang.Double southWestLat,
                      java.lang.Double northEastLng,
                      java.lang.Double northEastLat)
        Provides the geocoder with a hint to the region that the query resides in. This value will restrict the possible results to the supplied region. The value of the bounds parameter should be specified as two coordinate points forming the south-west and north-east corners of a bounding box. For example: bounds=-0.563160,51.280430,0.278970,51.683979 (min lon, min lat, max lon, max lat). Values that are not valid coordinates are ignored.
        Parameters:
        southWestLng - south west longitude
        southWestLat - south west latitude
        northEastLng - north east longitude
        northEastLat - north east latitude
